erfa
------------------------------------------
This is the source code repository for ERFA (Essential Routines for
Fundamental Astronomy). ERFA is a C library containing key algorithms for
astronomy, and is based on the SOFA library published by the International
Astronomical Union (IAU).

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.3.1-1
  liberfa-devel-1.2.0-1bl1
  liberfa1-1.2.0-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-4
  cygport-0.20.2-1
  gcc-core-4.9.3-1
  libtool-2.4.6-2
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/liberfa/erfa

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/liberfa/erfa/archive/v1.2.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack erfa-1.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./erfa-1.2.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/erfa-1.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/erfa-1.2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/liberfa1-1.2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/liberfa-devel-1.2.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(erfa)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/erfa.README
  /usr/share/doc/erfa/INFO
  /usr/share/doc/erfa/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/erfa/README.rst
  /usr/share/doc/erfa/RELEASE.rst

(liberfa1)
  /usr/bin/cygerfa-1.dll

(liberfa-devel)
  /usr/include/erfa.h
  /usr/include/erfam.h
  /usr/lib/liberfa.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/erfa.pc

